 considering whether calling toString on a proxy in an assertion might trigger the Handler and potentially cause a hang. I think using AssertJ's isInstanceOf might be okay, but using isNotSameAs could be problematic. I’ve got to remember not to call methods on the wrapped result! It’s definitely a fine line to tread, and I want to ensure I'm doing it correctly to avoid runtime issues down the line.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class naming for tests**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to name test classes for inner helper classes, which likely compile to a format with a dollar sign ($) in the name, but the test class or file itself may not. I notice that existing tests already have inner classes, so I'll need to ensure I assert there are no hangs by not starting a thread. It’s all about striking the right balance here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_05JaYC50K79otXbfan0tuDAj|fc_038cc0f50d86b0b40169f976b00718819fab09c90e3688289a", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.java.dev.jna/jna-platform/5.3.1/src/test/java/net_java_dev_jna/jna_platform/DdemlUtilInnerMessageLoopWrapperTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage net_java_dev_jna.jna_platform;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Constructor;\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationHandler;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Proxy;\n\nimport com.sun.jna.platform.win32.Ddeml.HCONV;\nimport com.sun.jna.platform.win32.DdemlUtil;\nimport com.sun.jna.platform.win32.User32Util.MessageLoopThread;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotSame;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;\n\npublic class DdemlUtilInnerMessageLoopWrapperTest {\n    @Test\n    void invocationWrapsReturnedConnectionInMessageLoopProxies() throws Exception {\n        DdemlUtil.IDdeConnection connection = new DdemlUtil.DdeConnection(null, new HCONV());\n        DelegateOperations delegate = new DelegateOperationsImpl(connection);\n        InvocationHandler handler = newMessageLoopWrapper(delegate);\n        DelegateOperations proxy = newProxy(DelegateOperations.class, handler);\n\n        DdemlUtil.IDdeConnection wrappedConnection = proxy.connection();\n\n        assertNotSame(connection, wrappedConnection);\n        assertTrue(Proxy.isProxyClass(wrappedConnection.getClass()));\n    }\n\n    private static InvocationHandler newMessageLoopWrapper(Object delegate) throws Exception {\n        Class<?> wrapperClass = Class.forName(\"com.sun.jna.platform.win32.DdemlUtil$MessageLoopWrapper\");\n        Constructor<?> constructor = wrapperClass.getDeclaredConstructor(MessageLoopThread.class, Object.class);\n        constructor.setAccessible(true);\n        return (InvocationHandler) constructor.newInstance(new MessageLoopThread(), delegate);\n    }\n\n    private static <T> T newProxy(Class<T> type, InvocationHandler handler) {\n        Object proxy = Proxy.newProxyInstance(\n                DdemlUtilInnerMessageLoopWrapperTest.class.getClassLoader(),\n                new Class<?>[] { type },\n                handler);\n        return type.cast(proxy);\n    }\n\n    public interface DelegateOperations {\n        DdemlUtil.IDdeConnection connection();\n    }\n\n    private static class DelegateOperationsImpl implements DelegateOperations {\n        private final DdemlUtil.IDdeConnection connection;\n\n        DelegateOperationsImpl(DdemlUtil.IDdeConnection connection) {\n            this.connection = connection;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public DdemlUtil.IDdeConnection connection() {\n            return connection;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1535, "output": 2202, "cacheRead": 34304, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38041, "cost":